                                <td class="confluenceTd">
                                        <p><strong>RCA:</strong> <img class="editor-inline-macro"
                                                        src="./Feb2026_files/macro(5)" data-macro-name="jira"
                                                        data-macro-id="232931d2-39fb-4b9c-a508-f793f65150f0"
                                                        role="button" tabindex="0" aria-haspopup="true"
                                                        aria-label="jira macro"
                                                        data-macro-parameters="key=RCA-5686|server=Granicus Jira"
                                                        data-macro-schema-version="1"> &nbsp;|&nbsp;
                                                <strong>Follow-up:</strong> <img class="editor-inline-macro"
                                                        src="./Feb2026_files/macro(6)" data-macro-name="jira"
                                                        data-macro-id="49dc7351-8744-4109-b79d-bafef1c3fce5"
                                                        role="button" tabindex="0" aria-haspopup="true"
                                                        aria-label="jira macro"
                                                        data-macro-parameters="key=SA-133859|server=Granicus Jira"
                                                        data-macro-schema-version="1"> <img class="editor-inline-macro"
                                                        src="./Feb2026_files/macro(7)" data-macro-name="jira"
                                                        data-macro-id="ca1ec728-ba3c-4688-8900-be1a66c7cc36"
                                                        role="button" tabindex="0" aria-haspopup="true"
                                                        aria-label="jira macro"
                                                        data-macro-parameters="key=SRE-17741|server=Granicus Jira"
                                                        data-macro-schema-version="1">
                                        </p>
                                        <p>Azure App Gateway platform update caused an HTTP/2 stream handling defect.
                                                App Gateway advertised correct Content-Length (965,447 bytes) but
                                                prematurely terminated stream after delivering only ~523,849 bytes
                                                (45.7% data loss). All 6 backend servers healthy and returning complete
                                                responses — truncation occurred exclusively at App Gateway
                                                layer.<br><strong>Incident Start:</strong> 05/Feb/26 6:25 AM |
                                                <strong>Awareness:</strong> 9:44 AM | <strong>Fixed:</strong> 6:30 PM |
                                                <strong>MTTA: 199m / MTTR: 725m (12.1
                                                        hrs)</strong><br><strong>Cause:</strong> Third Party
                                                Defect<br><strong>Customers impacted:</strong> 22 customers — OKC, LA
                                                City, Palo Alto, Miami Beach, Santa Clara County (Sev 2 override —
                                                "escalating based on number of customer reports and importance of
                                                impacted feature, which is both core and heavily
                                                utilized").<br><br><strong>Ticket comments:</strong><br>&#8226;
                                                <em>Chase House (SRE, 05/Feb/26):</em> Identified HTTP/2 truncation by
                                                testing all 6 backend servers directly (all returned 965,447 bytes
                                                complete) vs. through App Gateway (consistently ~523,849 bytes). Opened
                                                Azure Support ticket 2602050030007972 with evidence.<br>&#8226;
                                                <em>Azure:</em> Identified and rolled back platform-level changes to App
                                                Gateways causing the issue. Post-rollback confirmed normal.<br>&#8226;
                                                <em>DBA-9502</em> (MSSQL triage): DB layer confirmed healthy throughout
                                                — not a DB issue.
                                        </p>

                                </td>
                                <td class="confluenceTd"><strong>Immediate:</strong> SRE isolated the issue by testing
                                        the API endpoint directly against all 6 backend servers (all returned complete
                                        965,447-byte responses) vs. through the App Gateway (consistently truncated to
                                        ~523,849 bytes). Identified the Content-Length mismatch in HTTP/2 response
                                        headers. Opened Azure Support ticket 2602050030007972 and escalated with
                                        evidence. Azure rolled back the platform-level App Gateway update (Feb 5 evening
                                        CT), restoring normal service.<br><br><strong>Follow-up Actions:</strong><br>•
                                        <strong>SA-133859</strong> (DevOps, Chitresh Das): Audit Cloudflare WAF rules to
                                        prevent masking upstream vendor issues in future — <em>Status: Ready</em><br>•
                                        <strong>SRE-17741</strong> (SRE, Unassigned): Create edge-vs-origin isolation
                                        playbook to reduce triage time in similar incidents — <em>Status: Open</em>
                                </td>
                                <td class="confluenceTd"><img class="editor-inline-macro" height="18" width="88"
                                                src="./Feb2026_files/placeholder(3)" data-macro-name="status"
                                                data-macro-id="332cd3ce-0c80-4181-b11d-37be837165b7" role="button"
                                                tabindex="0" aria-haspopup="true" aria-label="3rd Party status macro"
                                                data-macro-parameters="colour=Purple|title=3rd Party"
                                                data-macro-schema-version="1"><br><strong>What happened:</strong> 22
                                        customers (OKC, LA City, Palo Alto, Miami Beach, Santa Clara County) experienced
                                        intermittent failures where tasks/forms/workflows returned HTTP 200 with
                                        truncated JSON (965KB truncated to 523KB - 45.7% data loss). Azure App Gateway
                                        HTTP/2 stream defect after platform update. 8h 53m war room (9:57 AM - 6:50 PM
                                        CT).<br><strong>Follow-up:</strong> Azure Support ticket 2602050030007972
                                        opened. Vendor rolled back App Gateway update evening of Feb 5. Formal Azure RCA
                                        requested. SA-133859 (Cloudflare WAF audit), SRE-17741 (edge-vs-origin isolation
                                        playbook) created.<br><strong>Blocker:</strong> None - resolved by Azure
                                        rollback. Awaiting vendor RCA documentation.</td>
