                                                        aria-label="jira macro"
                                                        data-macro-parameters="key=RCA-5734|server=Granicus Jira"
                                                        data-macro-schema-version="1"> &nbsp;|&nbsp;
                                                <strong>Problem:</strong> <img class="editor-inline-macro"
                                                        src="./Feb2026_files/macro(11)" data-macro-name="jira"
                                                        data-macro-id="c6976639-5028-4e21-97a2-41d862e34d50"
                                                        role="button" tabindex="0" aria-haspopup="true"
                                                        aria-label="jira macro"
                                                        data-macro-parameters="key=RUN-117696|server=Granicus Jira"
                                                        data-macro-schema-version="1"> | <img
                                                        class="editor-inline-macro" src="./Feb2026_files/macro(10)"
                                                        data-macro-name="jira"
                                                        data-macro-id="1c4e919e-14cd-48bd-a240-77e7c4efbfa8"
                                                        role="button" tabindex="0" aria-haspopup="true"
                                                        aria-label="jira macro"
                                                        data-macro-parameters="key=SA-130780|server=Granicus Jira"
                                                        data-macro-schema-version="1">
                                        </p>
                                        <p>Swagit Admin V3 failed to create video mastering points for new meetings due
                                                to network/TCP connectivity failures between application and backend
                                                services ('hlsjs-lite: Network error'). Coincided with cache saturation
                                                and high volume utilization on Wowza/archive servers
                                                (aasmp-wowarch1–aasmp-wowarch10). Restarting WowzaStreamingEngine
                                                cleared cache and restored TCP connectivity.<br><strong>Incident
                                                        Start:</strong> 10/Feb/26 7:08 PM | <strong>Awareness:</strong>
                                                7:09 PM | <strong>Fixed:</strong> 7:42 PM | <strong>MTTA: 1m / MTTR:
                                                        34m</strong><br><strong>Cause:</strong> Operational Capacity —
                                                Wowza cache saturation<br><strong>Customers impacted:</strong> All
                                                GovMeetings Swagit customers relying on same-day video posting. Kyle
                                                White: "every indexer" impacted; multiple clients affected; customers
                                                could not see newly recorded meetings posted during
                                                window.<br><br><strong>Ticket comments:</strong><br>&#8226; <em>Kyle
                                                        White (10/Feb/26):</em> "Indexers started reporting around 5:30
                                                PM CT that we are getting 'hlsjs-lite: Network error' whenever we try to
                                                Master any hours or when we select hours to try and Index. This is
                                                affecting all clients in V3 as far as we can tell."<br>&#8226;
                                                <em>Edrich Lewis (SRE, 10/Feb/26):</em> Restarted WowzaStreamingEngine
                                                on all wowza servers aasmp-wowarch1 through aasmp-wowarch10. After
                                                restart of service, issue was resolved.<br>&#8226; <em>Kyle White
                                                        confirmed</em> indexers could successfully master and post
                                                meeting videos post-restart.<br>&#8226; <em>SA-130780</em> (Jacob
                                                Odell): MediaCache Config Optimization — waiting on updated Ubuntu 20.04
                                                vSphere template (SA-133904). Existing SOP in place for manual cache
                                                clearance.
                                        </p>
                                </td>
                                <td class="confluenceTd"><strong>Immediate:</strong> SRE restarted WowzaStreamingEngine
                                        service on all Wowza/archive servers (aasmp-wowarch1 through aasmp-wowarch10).
                                        Cache cleared post-restart, TCP connectivity restored. Kyle White confirmed
                                        indexers could successfully master and post meeting videos. Database tier was
                                        healthy throughout the incident — issue was isolated to the Wowza application
                                        layer.<br><br><strong>Follow-up Actions:</strong><br>•
                                        <strong>SA-130780</strong> (DevOps, Jacob Odell): MediaCache Configuration
                                        Optimization — investigate and implement permanent fix for Wowza /var/mediacache
                                        partition to prevent future cache saturation. Existing SOP in place for manual
                                        cache clearance. — <em>Status: Waiting on other (blocked on updated Ubuntu 20.04
                                                vSphere template, SA-133904)</em><br>• <strong>RUN-117696</strong>
                                        (Problem ticket, Unassigned): Track recurring Wowza/MediaCache cache saturation
                                        and Admin V3 failures to identify patterns — <em>Status: Open</em>
                                </td>
                                <td class="confluenceTd"><img class="editor-inline-macro" height="18" width="88"
                                                src="./Feb2026_files/placeholder(4)" data-macro-name="status"
                                                data-macro-id="29f33136-83d7-40b8-8f90-e26bcee3b9bd" role="button"
                                                tabindex="0" aria-haspopup="true"
                                                aria-label="High Priority status macro"
                                                data-macro-parameters="colour=Red|title=High Priority"
                                                data-macro-schema-version="1"><br><strong>What happened:</strong> Every
                                        Swagit indexer impacted on busiest day (Tuesday). Admin V3 failed to master/post
                                        same-day meeting videos for 2h 15m (5:30-7:45 PM CST). Network errors ("no route
                                        to host") coincided with Wowza/archive servers running cache &gt;100%.
                                        Previously posted content remained available.<br><strong>Follow-up:</strong>
                                        SA-130780 (MediaCache/Wowza storage tuning) assigned to Jacob Odell. RUN-117696
                                        (Problem ticket) tracking recurring cache issues. Existing SOP used for service
                                        restart.<br><strong>Blocker:</strong> None - incident resolved. Long-term
                                        storage optimization in progress.</td>
                        </tr>
