                                </td>
                                <td class="confluenceTd">
                                        <p><strong>RCA:</strong> <img class="editor-inline-macro"
                                                        src="./Feb2026_files/macro(13)" data-macro-name="jira"
                                                        data-macro-id="34529060-7f95-4272-9066-06847523352b"
                                                        role="button" tabindex="0" aria-haspopup="true"
                                                        aria-label="jira macro"
                                                        data-macro-parameters="key=RCA-5667|server=Granicus Jira"
                                                        data-macro-schema-version="1"></p>
                                        <p>SpeakUp webserver high CPU utilization due to slow MongoDB ideas find query
                                                for Controller/profile/comments transaction. Legitimate traffic from
                                                denver.granicusideas.com caused spike.<br><strong>Incident
                                                        Start:</strong> 03/Feb/26 5:07 AM | <strong>Awareness:</strong>
                                                5:08 AM | <strong>Fixed:</strong> 5:13 AM | <strong>MTTA: 1m / MTTR:
                                                        6m</strong><br><strong>Cause:</strong> Operational
                                                Capacity<br><strong>Customers impacted:</strong> No — Performance
                                                Degradation, product available. Non-peak hours.<br><br><strong>Ticket
                                                        comments:</strong><br>&#8226; <em>Shrikant Dandge
                                                        (03/Feb/26):</em> "The traffic looks legitimate as the origin of
                                                top transactions were from denver.granicusideas.com. Need some
                                                investigation from MongoDB side between period 5:09 AM CDT to 5:11 CDT."
                                                Slow query: Total duration: 74,144 ms | Call count: 66 | GET_MORE on
                                                civicideas-us-production.ideas collection
                                                (cursor_id=98860241024).<br>&#8226; <em>Shrikant Dandge
                                                        (03/Feb/26):</em> "There was a spike in incoming requests on
                                                speakup webservers. Controller/profile/comments transaction was
                                                slowest." NR APM data confirmed.<br>&#8226; <em>Vijayeendra Kolhapur
                                                        (03/Feb/26):</em> "Alert cleared as soon as the incident was
                                                generated."<br>&#8226; <strong>SpeakUp monitored on New Relic
                                                        only</strong> — Sheldon Rampton is sole NR access holder for
                                                investigation. Known monitoring gap.</p>
                                </td>
                                <td class="confluenceTd"><strong>Immediate:</strong> Auto-resolved within 6 minutes of
                                        alert. No manual intervention was required. Monitoring performed as designed —
                                        alert cleared as soon as system recovered.<br><br><strong>Root cause
                                                context:</strong> MongoDB ideas find query (GET_MORE on
                                        civicideas-us-production.ideas collection) took 74,144ms total across 66 calls —
                                        likely a cursor exhaustion scenario under high legitimate
                                        traffic.<br><br><strong>Follow-up:</strong> Investigate adding a MongoDB
                                        slow-query alert specific to the Controller/profile/comments transaction to
                                        provide earlier warning. SpeakUp is still monitored via New Relic (not yet on
                                        Elastic). Only Sheldon Rampton has NR access for investigation — this is a known
                                        monitoring gap.</td>
                                <td class="confluenceTd"><strong>Status: ✅ DONE
                                                (auto-resolved)</strong><br><br><strong>What happened:</strong> Feb 3,
                                        5:07–5:13 AM CT. Spike in legitimate traffic from denver.granicusideas.com hit
                                        SpeakUp webservers. MongoDB query for Controller/profile/comments transaction
                                        spiked to 74.1s total duration (66 calls), causing high CPU and brief service
                                        degradation. Reported internally by monitor (PagerDuty). MTTA: 1m / MTTR:
                                        6m.<br><br><strong>Is it done?</strong> Yes — auto-resolved. Alert cleared
                                        within 6 minutes.<br><strong>Blocked?</strong> No immediate blocker. However,
                                        long-term: SpeakUp is not yet on Elastic (still NR-only), meaning root cause
                                        investigation requires Sheldon Rampton's NR access. This is an open monitoring
                                        gap.<br><strong>Who is blocking?</strong> NR decommission is on hold — SpeakUp
                                        onboarding to Elastic not yet done.<br><strong>Who needs to unblock?</strong>
                                        DevOps / RS DevOps team to onboard SpeakUp APM to Elastic.</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
