        <h2 style="color: rgb(200,0,0);">⚠️ SpeakUp — Application at Risk (Roadmap Needed)</h2>
        <ul>
                <li><strong>Still monitored in New Relic (not Elastic)</strong> — old Ruby version incompatible with
                        Elastic agent. NR decommission on hold.</li>
                <li><strong>MongoDB version very old — no upgrades possible</strong>; 50M+ DB users with anonymous
                        comments. Cursor exhaustion and slow queries recurring.</li>
                <li><strong>Recurring performance issues in Feb 2026:</strong> Feb 3 slow MongoDB query (RUN-117083),
                        Feb 5 host socket errors (RUN-117382), Feb 27 spam traffic brief outage (RUN-119192). Same root
                        pattern: spam users drive excessive profile/comments traffic with no application-layer block.
                </li>
                <li><strong>Degradation of SpeakUp can impact Legistar/iLegislate</strong> — downstream dependency risk.
                </li>
                <li><strong>Akamai WAF advanced features may help</strong> but require Dev engagement (SRE-13863 —
                        requires Gerry's Approval, currently BLOCKED).</li>
                <li><strong>Long-term: SpeakUp application replacement is the only complete fix.</strong> No code
                        changes in flight for spam blocking. Engineering/Product leadership must prioritize.</li>
        </ul>

